1
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:29,980
=The Youth Memories=

2
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:32,980
=Episode 26=

3
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:42,120
My daughter wasn't willing to

4
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:45,960
play elsewhere other than

5
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,440
in my study when she was little.

6
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:50,960
At that time,

7
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:51,840
she was only this tall.

8
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:54,520
She was having fun
in my study in her free time.

9
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:56,760
I picked

10
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:58,240
one of her mom's medical books

11
00:01:58,360 --> 00:01:59,040
and gave it to her.

12
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,440
I didn't think too much.

13
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:01,800
However, after a while,

14
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,960
she raised her head
and asked me a question.

15
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,720
Superior nasal concha.
Superior nasal meatus.

16
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:07,940
(Sphenoethmoidal recess)

17
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:08,960
Dad.

18
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:12,160
What is sphenoethmoidal recess?

19
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:18,120
That's my daughter.

20
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:21,680
When she's determined,

21
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:23,960
no one can stop her.

22
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:27,160
She looked like this

23
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,520
when she decided to study medicine.

24
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:30,200
And she now looks like this too

25
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:33,880
when she

26
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:35,440
chooses you.

27
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:39,960
Now I understand.

28
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:41,720
She's determined

29
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,520
to choose you.

30
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:45,920
Of course,

31
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,560
I've also heard

32
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:50,920
that you

33
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:52,360
have several brothers

34
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:55,400
and you had a girlfriend before.

35
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:58,680
Mr. Tong...

36
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:00,160
You don't need to explain it now.

37
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:02,360
What is done is done.

38
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:04,240
However,

39
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,520
when we were eating today,

40
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,560
my wife and I could tell

41
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,560
how much Xiaomei loves you

42
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,480
from her eyes.

43
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,680
We were once young too

44
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,440
and we know what's happening.

45
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:21,600
Mr. Tong,

46
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:22,920
don't worry.

47
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:24,920
I will always take care

48
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,920
of Xiaomei.

49
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,360
I trust you.

50
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:34,920
However,

51
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:38,120
times have changed.

52
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:39,320
Things are changing fast

53
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,600
and there are lots of opportunities

54
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:42,760
and temptations.

55
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:44,640
They come into our lives

56
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:46,000
from different directions

57
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:48,360
in various waves.

58
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,000
Xiaomei said

59
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:53,120
that you're a man

60
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:54,600
of ideals and ambition.

61
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:56,520
This is good.

62
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,280
However,

63
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:01,880
society is different from the army.

64
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,440
Whether you can stick

65
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,840
to your ideals in this society

66
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,240
is another question.

67
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:09,120
I have faith in myself.

68
00:04:21,830 --> 00:04:22,560
Have you seen it?

69
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:24,720
A new watch.

70
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:29,000
Is this Longines?

71
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:30,160
Yeah.

72
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,680
It's sold out in the whole city.

73
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,480
Where did you buy it?

74
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,000
In Shanghai.

75
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:37,920
My daughter was there on a business trip

76
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,720
and it took her a lot of effort to buy one.

77
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,200
Stop showing off.

78
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,600
Now, Titoni and Rado

79
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:44,760
are the best watchmakers in the country.

80
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,320
Is yours better than them?

81
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:50,120
How can they compare to his?

82
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:52,160
The TV commercial says

83
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,000
that you can travel the world
with a Longines watch.

84
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:58,480
I've never seen Titoni watches on TV.

85
00:04:58,480 --> 00:04:59,080
Enough.

86
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:02,000
Those who sell foreign goods
have the money to advertise

87
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:04,360
and the commercials boost their sales.

88
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:06,160
With more sales, they're even richer.

89
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:07,680
I don't have money to advertise,

90
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,000
so I can't sell much

91
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:10,240
and won't have much money.

92
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,640
What's going on now?

93
00:05:11,960 --> 00:05:13,640
It's all about money.

94
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:16,160
Isn't this capitalism?

95
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,680
I think if the government
doesn't intervene,

96
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,240
then we're doomed sooner or later.

97
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:21,680
It's not that bad.

98
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:23,080
Calm down, please.

99
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,760
We just want to live a good life,

100
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,240
we don't think this much.

101
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:29,400
Why are you still so moralistic?

102
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:31,960
He's just dogmatic.

103
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:33,440
That's the most reactionary.

104
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:35,920
The collective economy

105
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:37,960
has gone.

106
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:39,520
It's all about competitions now.

107
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:41,160
They just make commercials

108
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:43,680
to let you know
that there's such a product.

109
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:46,960
People won't buy it if it's not good.

110
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:49,680
Yeah, right.
We have a market economy now.

111
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:51,320
Exactly. Market economy.

112
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:55,720
You...

113
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:57,800
No, you can't cheat...

114
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:10,440
Here you are.

115
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:13,080
Sir,

116
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:14,720
we didn't order this.

117
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:15,640
This is for free.

118
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:17,600
No need for me to introduce him.

119
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:18,440
This is Qi Tian.

120
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:21,040
Tian, this is the Shrimp,
my childhood friend.

121
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,760
He's a senior chef now.

122
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:24,720
You flatter me.

123
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:27,160
Tian, I should raise

124
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:28,400
a toast to you today,

125
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:29,600
unfortunately,

126
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,640
I'm not allowed to drink at work.

127
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:34,320
Okay, I won't bother you then.

128
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:36,320
I'm not busy at all.

129
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:36,880
Look.

130
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:38,720
We don't even have customers now.

131
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:43,120
But the business was doing well
when I came here a while ago.

132
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:44,720
It's not doing well anymore.

133
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:46,120
Now,

134
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,240
nobody eats in old
state-run restaurants anymore.

135
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:51,160
There are lots of new restaurants
in Xidan and Wangfujing

136
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:52,160
and people go there.

137
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:55,120
Do you remember Wu?

138
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:59,000
Wu has opened a shop in Wangfujing,

139
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:00,240
selling flatbread and meat.

140
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,840
The shop thrives.

141
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:05,240
The one who's pigeon-toed?

142
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:07,520
You're still looking down on Wu?

143
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,240
Much has changed.

144
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:14,120
Our old friends

145
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,400
are living comfortable lives

146
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,920
by running clothing stores

147
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,640
or repair shops.

148
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:21,400
By the way,

149
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,520
there's another person.

150
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:23,880
And you both know him.

151
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:25,640
Who?

152
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:26,920
Li Shangyou.

153
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,000
Now he's very successful.

154
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:30,560
He owns big businesses.

155
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:32,240
A piece he wears

156
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,440
is worth 10,000 yuan at least.

157
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,520
When you see him,
you have to bow down too.

158
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:39,560
Whatever.

159
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:42,200
In the end, I have to bow down anyway.

160
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:44,280
To whom?

161
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:45,720
To life!

162
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:49,880
Good.

163
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:51,200
You're mature now.

164
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:52,640
Well,

165
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,360
I'll leave you alone.

166
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:55,440
Enjoy.

167
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:02,880
Chunsheng, it's been more than
half a year since your recovery.

168
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:04,600
What's your plan?

169
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,320
I haven't decided yet.

170
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:09,960
I know a way to make money.

171
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,880
Do you want to join me?

172
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:13,640
What way to make money?

173
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:18,760
Imported cigarettes.

174
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,520
Ye Fang, I mean,

175
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,480
today you have to explain

176
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,200
why you don't want me

177
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,150
to recruit Chunsheng
to the Anti-smuggling Squad.

178
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:38,640
I mean, I don't understand it.

179
00:08:38,910 --> 00:08:40,880
I know you didn't like Chunsheng

180
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:41,480
before.

181
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:42,840
However, he's dating

182
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,400
your good friend Tong Xiaomei now.

183
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,120
Maybe you should change your mind.

184
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:50,000
Listen,

185
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:52,200
it's been more than half a year
since Chunsheng's recovery.

186
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,000
He has to have a job.

187
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:54,920
And the Customs

188
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,720
happens to establish
the Anti-smuggling Squad now.

189
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:59,040
Veterans in their prime
are our top choice.

190
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:01,400
I think Chunsheng
suits this job very well

191
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,400
and I believe he will be good.

192
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:04,840
If he gets the job,

193
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:07,280
then we will be colleagues again

194
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,240
working for counterparts
of different levels.

195
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,880
Isn't that nice?

196
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:11,880
I said I'd ask,

197
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,560
and you didn't even
want me to mention it.

198
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:16,560
Don't you think you're too bossy?

199
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,200
Ye Fang,

200
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:28,560
listen,

201
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:29,720
I'm really getting a bit angry.

202
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:31,240
Putting other things aside,

203
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:32,720
let's talk about having children.

204
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:33,720
You don't want children

205
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:35,240
and I'm okay with that.

206
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:36,600
However, my mom

207
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,000
has talked to me
so many times about this.

208
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,080
There's nothing I could do,

209
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,120
I could only retort upon her.

210
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:40,680
And after that,

211
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:42,280
your mom came to
persuade me to have a child.

212
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:43,200
However,

213
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,560
this is not something I can decide alone.

214
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:47,160
You even have good reasons

215
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:48,240
for not having children.

216
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:50,400
Then why are you
so against Chunsheng getting this job?

217
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,280
Why?

218
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:52,640
I agree!

219
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:55,880
What did you say?

220
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:57,320
I said I agree.

221
00:09:58,240 --> 00:09:59,480
Go to tell Chunsheng.

222
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:01,040
Okay, thank you, darling.

223
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:02,320
I'll call Chunsheng now.

224
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,040
Go ahead.

225
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,320
Maybe he will say no.

226
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:08,400
That's impossible.

227
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,520
No matter whether he agrees or not,

228
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:11,760
the only thing I can tell you

229
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,400
is that you will surely
regret it in the future.

230
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:23,560
Chunsheng,

231
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:27,160
I've figured it out during this time.

232
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:28,680
Imported cigarettes

233
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:31,080
are the most lucrative.

234
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:34,440
First, everyone wants
to try the new cigarettes.

235
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,720
They're in great demand in small shops.

236
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,280
Most importantly,
they're highly profitable.

237
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:41,640
In the end,

238
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:42,760
profit matters the most.

239
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,680
We're not young anymore.

240
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:50,480
It's time for me to be a father now.

241
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:52,200
I have to work harder.

242
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,760
You and Xiaomei have also met

243
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:58,280
each other's parents.

244
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,720
You two will get married sooner or later.

245
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:04,360
After you get married,

246
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:06,720
you'll know that
you need money everywhere.

247
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:10,520
That makes sense,

248
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:12,120
however,

249
00:11:13,160 --> 00:11:15,960
is it legal to trade
in imported cigarettes now?

250
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:18,800
It's not declared illegal,

251
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:22,160
so let's take it as legal.

252
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:26,480
Also, I received my sales license

253
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:28,680
through lawful means.

254
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,360
So what's the problem?

255
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:31,200
Right?

256
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:34,760
Then what about the purchase channel?

257
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,040
Is it risky?

258
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:39,480
Tian, listen.

259
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:42,480
You're different from before.

260
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:43,840
I know.

261
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:46,560
I'm only in charge of the sales.

262
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,360
Heizi is the one

263
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:51,640
who purchases the cigarettes.

264
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:55,480
Heizi is not doing well either now,

265
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:58,360
let's help him if we can,

266
00:11:58,760 --> 00:11:59,320
okay?

267
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:06,680
If you're

268
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:08,640
interested,

269
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:10,960
then you can join me at any time.

270
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:13,240
Anyway, I've told you

271
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:15,160
the secrets about it.

272
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:19,160
Okay. Let's drink.

273
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:20,200
Cheers.

274
00:12:26,780 --> 00:12:30,540
(Guangzhou Railway Station)

275
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:40,720
Brother.

276
00:12:41,040 --> 00:12:41,520
Um...

277
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:44,560
A gold ring, a gold watch.

278
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:45,960
Are you rich now?

279
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:49,720
Tell me

280
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:51,200
how you got rich.

281
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:53,760
Buying and selling.

282
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:55,960
Yes. I've heard of it.

283
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:58,600
You got this rich

284
00:12:58,960 --> 00:12:59,800
by buying goods in Shenzhen
and selling them in Beijing?

285
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,640
You're only scratching the surface.

286
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:06,280
When I first arrived,
this was what I did.

287
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:09,200
I bought goods in Shenzhen
and sold them in Beijing

288
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,360
to earn a small amount of money.

